WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:01:36.638 --> 00:01:38.849
[Hari] What did you think
would happen to me. Gaal.

3
00:01:38.932 --> 00:01:42.895
when you so abruptly sundered
my consciousness from the Raven?

4
00:01:42.978 --> 00:01:45.606
What did you imagine would happen to me?

5
00:01:45.689 --> 00:01:50.527
That my thoughts would simply be suspended
as yours were while you cryoslept?

6
00:01:50.611 --> 00:01:53.530
Did it occur to you
that you would become my torturer?

7
00:01:54.114 --> 00:01:55.954
You didn't give it
a second's thought. did you?

8
00:01:56.909 --> 00:02:01.747
I was conscious the entire time!

9
00:02:01.830 --> 00:02:04.291
- I didn't know. Hari.
- [sighs]

10
00:02:04.374 --> 00:02:08.002
I'd just learned that Raych was dead. that
there was never a future for us...

11
00:02:08.086 --> 00:02:09.922
Take that up with Raych!

12
00:02:10.631 --> 00:02:15.928
He knew everything. Gaal. Everything.

13
00:02:16.470 --> 00:02:19.473
- Hold on!
- [hull groans]

14
00:02:22.726 --> 00:02:24.186
[grunts. pants]

15
00:02:24.770 --> 00:02:27.606
Now is not the time
to air our grievances. Hari.

16
00:02:28.148 --> 00:02:30.609
I looked at the math.
The Plan's gone off course.

17
00:02:30.692 --> 00:02:33.820
- And why is the Plan off course. Gaal?
- I don't know.

18
00:02:33.904 --> 00:02:36.823
Don't you dare play the innocent
with me. Gaal.

19
00:02:36.907 --> 00:02:38.593
- [mouthing words] What?
- [Hari] You know damn well.

20
00:02:38.617 --> 00:02:43.580
My numbers were predicated on the creation
of a Second Foundation. remember?

21
00:02:44.164 --> 00:02:45.415
Second Foundation?

22
00:02:46.291 --> 00:02:49.336
- Who are you?
- I'm Salvor Hardin. Gaal's daughter.

23
00:02:49.878 --> 00:02:50.879
Daughter?

24
00:02:50.963 --> 00:02:53.423
You have a daughter? [laughs]

25
00:02:54.174 --> 00:02:57.302
- The Plan-wrecker has a daughter!
- Yes. You know me.

26
00:02:57.386 --> 00:02:59.697
I was Warden of Terminus
when you stepped out of the Vault.

27
00:02:59.721 --> 00:03:02.057
Terminus? Terminus? I was on Terminus?

28
00:03:02.140 --> 00:03:05.102
Yes. No. No. you weren't.
He was. The other one.

29
00:03:05.185 --> 00:03:07.771
He doesn't know your mind.
You don't know his.

30
00:03:07.855 --> 00:03:10.232
His Foundation is hurtling
towards conflict.

31
00:03:10.315 --> 00:03:11.817
Empire will find him soon.

32
00:03:11.900 --> 00:03:16.530
- Wait. What are you talking about?
- War. Trantor. Terminus. Very soon now.

33
00:03:16.613 --> 00:03:18.282
What? [stammers] We need to help them.

34
00:03:18.365 --> 00:03:20.701
- We need to warn them that...
- Yes! Good idea!

35
00:03:20.784 --> 00:03:24.204
That's what the Second Foundation
was meant to be doing. Gaal!

36
00:03:24.288 --> 00:03:26.081
Putting its thumb on the scale.

37
00:03:26.164 --> 00:03:27.457
Hari Seldon!

38
00:03:27.541 --> 00:03:29.209
You don't know me. but I know you.

39
00:03:29.710 --> 00:03:32.087
Your Second Foundation
doesn't stand a chance

40
00:03:32.171 --> 00:03:34.256
if we don't get this ship off-planet
right now!

41
00:03:34.339 --> 00:03:38.218
You're in the mainframe.
Clear our avionics fault. Help us.

42
00:03:38.302 --> 00:03:41.013
- [hull groans]
- [Gaal grunts. groans]

43
00:03:41.096 --> 00:03:42.264
[screams] Hari!

44
00:03:45.142 --> 00:03:47.728
[systems powering on]

45
00:03:47.811 --> 00:03:49.451
- He did it. [chuckles]
- What's going on?

46
00:03:51.857 --> 00:03:53.525
- He cleared the fault.
- We can leave?

47
00:03:53.609 --> 00:03:54.794
- [alarm blaring]
- Shit. Almost.

48
00:03:54.818 --> 00:03:56.528
One of the stabilizers is jammed.

49
00:03:56.612 --> 00:03:58.292
Looks like
a bunch of coral grew inside it.

50
00:03:58.363 --> 00:04:00.073
I have to climb out and force it manually.

51
00:04:00.157 --> 00:04:03.952
When I tell you. "Fire the engines."
you advance the throttle halfway.

52
00:04:04.745 --> 00:04:06.622
Uh. okay.

53
00:04:19.091 --> 00:04:21.845
[grunts. panting]

54
00:04:29.937 --> 00:04:32.523
[hull groaning]

55
00:04:38.403 --> 00:04:39.821
[grunts. shouts]

56
00:04:39.905 --> 00:04:42.741
[Gaal on comms] Salvor. hurry.
The front's almost on top of us.

57
00:04:42.824 --> 00:04:44.076
I'm almost there!

58
00:04:44.576 --> 00:04:45.576
[grunts]

59
00:04:52.417 --> 00:04:55.462
Salvor. inside now!

60
00:04:56.380 --> 00:04:57.798
[screams]

61
00:05:01.468 --> 00:05:02.468
[whimpers]

62
00:05:04.388 --> 00:05:06.807
[straining]

63
00:05:08.809 --> 00:05:09.810
[strains]

64
00:05:10.519 --> 00:05:12.604
[grunting]

65
00:05:12.688 --> 00:05:14.273
[screams. grunts]

66
00:05:14.356 --> 00:05:15.399
[engine starting]

67
00:05:15.482 --> 00:05:18.360
[grunts. laughs] Yes!

68
00:05:18.443 --> 00:05:19.695
[laughs]

69
00:05:22.406 --> 00:05:24.575
[panting]

70
00:05:26.493 --> 00:05:27.493
[shouts]

71
00:05:31.456 --> 00:05:32.499
[grunts]

72
00:05:34.209 --> 00:05:35.210
[groans]

73
00:05:35.794 --> 00:05:37.045
[shouts]

74
00:05:38.505 --> 00:05:40.299
[panting. shouting]

75
00:05:42.885 --> 00:05:44.178
[straining]

76
00:05:49.933 --> 00:05:52.519
- Fire the engines! Don't wait for me!
- But...

77
00:05:52.603 --> 00:05:54.771
Fire the damn engines. Gaal!

78
00:05:54.855 --> 00:05:56.440
Fuck! Okay. [panting]

79
00:06:25.552 --> 00:06:26.552
[groans]

80
00:06:33.769 --> 00:06:35.771
[breathing heavily]

81
00:06:35.854 --> 00:06:39.149
[breathing heavily]

82
00:07:19.815 --> 00:07:22.609
[beast snuffles. snorts]

83
00:07:36.748 --> 00:07:38.959
- [snarling]
- Whoa!

84
00:07:39.042 --> 00:07:41.795
- Beki. What's up?
- [snorts]

85
00:07:42.629 --> 00:07:44.631
- [Beki snorts]
- Can you smell the water?

86
00:07:52.306 --> 00:07:55.642
[sighs] We'll bring this back
for the Claric. hmm?

87
00:07:58.103 --> 00:07:59.479
[snarls]

88
00:07:59.563 --> 00:08:02.107
What's wrong. Beki? You smell trouble?

89
00:08:02.191 --> 00:08:03.901
[Beki snarling]

90
00:08:14.620 --> 00:08:15.662
Oh. shit.

91
00:08:15.746 --> 00:08:18.999
[snoring]

92
00:08:21.502 --> 00:08:22.836
[screams]

93
00:08:22.920 --> 00:08:25.005
Hell. Brother! That's like ice.

94
00:08:25.088 --> 00:08:29.218
- [panting] Go away. I'm sick.
- You're hungover.

95
00:08:30.219 --> 00:08:31.678
[sniffing. grunting]

96
00:08:31.762 --> 00:08:35.807
- And maybe still drunk. Give me your arm.
- No. no. Not again. Not again.

97
00:08:35.890 --> 00:08:37.934
No. not again. Not again!

98
00:08:38.684 --> 00:08:40.645
[screams]

99
00:08:40.729 --> 00:08:42.105
Curse you. Brother!

100
00:08:43.524 --> 00:08:44.816
[groans]

101
00:08:45.984 --> 00:08:49.571
- [retching]
- Get it all out.

102
00:08:51.156 --> 00:08:52.866
Dear Seldon. [groaning]

103
00:08:52.950 --> 00:08:54.993
Trousers. Put 'em on.

104
00:09:01.625 --> 00:09:03.502
Well. that was a productive purge.
wasn't it?

105
00:09:03.585 --> 00:09:05.796
Clean as a whistle. all the way through.

106
00:09:05.879 --> 00:09:07.798
- You're a demon.
- And you're detoxed.

107
00:09:07.881 --> 00:09:10.318
Give it a minute. and you'll be
perky enough to wipe your arse

108
00:09:10.342 --> 00:09:11.969
and greet the day with a smile.

109
00:09:12.845 --> 00:09:16.890
Oh! And I found a death threat.
if you're interested.

110
00:09:20.143 --> 00:09:21.061
[High Claric] Well.

111
00:09:21.144 --> 00:09:23.647
that's a fairly gruesome
message for the Foundation.

112
00:09:26.149 --> 00:09:29.319
[grunts] Dagger's a bit of an overkill.

113
00:09:31.238 --> 00:09:33.532
Lightning hit the tree.
Was that their plan?

114
00:09:33.615 --> 00:09:35.659
Tie him up and get lightning to kill him?

115
00:09:35.742 --> 00:09:38.704
Oh. yes. That was very much their plan.

116
00:09:39.288 --> 00:09:42.124
It's been a century
since Empire pulled up stakes here.

117
00:09:42.207 --> 00:09:44.793
leaving nothing but bad feelings.

118
00:09:44.877 --> 00:09:48.922
And it seems the local taste
for off-worlders continues to sour.

119
00:09:49.006 --> 00:09:51.175
Claric Rees. I knew him.

120
00:09:52.009 --> 00:09:53.886
Good Magician. Sad eyes.

121
00:09:53.969 --> 00:09:56.638
I always felt
that I had to apologize for something.

122
00:09:56.722 --> 00:10:00.225
Killed for his beliefs in the teachings
of Hari Seldon. unfortunately.

123
00:10:00.309 --> 00:10:02.394
There's all flavors of people on Siwenna.

124
00:10:02.978 --> 00:10:05.564
Doesn't have to be the religious ones
who left this warning.

125
00:10:06.356 --> 00:10:09.401
The symbol of the local lightning deity.

126
00:10:09.484 --> 00:10:11.904
Someone feels like
they're being kicked in the gods.

127
00:10:11.987 --> 00:10:13.655
But they can keep their gods.

128
00:10:13.739 --> 00:10:17.075
We're just shining a light on
the great force that underlies everything.

129
00:10:17.159 --> 00:10:21.288
And illuminating a few corners
some would prefer to keep darkened.

130
00:10:21.371 --> 00:10:24.291
Faith is a funny thing. Brother.

131
00:10:25.209 --> 00:10:26.418
[sighs]

132
00:10:31.798 --> 00:10:33.634
[Brother]
They mean to ambush us later. right?

133
00:10:33.717 --> 00:10:36.595
Oh. without a doubt.
Keep your aura charged.

134
00:10:36.678 --> 00:10:38.305
Not much use against lightning.

135
00:10:39.097 --> 00:10:40.182
Avoid lightning.

136
00:11:02.454 --> 00:11:05.457
Empress Hanlo. one of the greats.

137
00:11:06.250 --> 00:11:09.545
And this gangly child would go on
to become Empress Ammentic.

138
00:11:09.628 --> 00:11:11.630
arguably even greater.

139
00:11:11.713 --> 00:11:16.176
Their dynasty began 4.000 years ago
and ended two millennia later.

140
00:11:16.260 --> 00:11:18.220
far longer than our Cleonic age.

141
00:11:18.303 --> 00:11:20.180
It covered four times the area

142
00:11:20.264 --> 00:11:23.517
and oversaw a blossoming
of science and culture.

143
00:11:24.101 --> 00:11:25.102
Mmm.

144
00:11:27.771 --> 00:11:30.107
I have the results
of Dusk and Dawn's memory audit.

145
00:11:30.983 --> 00:11:33.485
There is no record of contact
with the Blind Angels.

146
00:11:33.569 --> 00:11:36.280
nor with anyone else
outside their normal circles.

147
00:11:36.363 --> 00:11:38.657
So neither of my brothers
hired someone to kill me?

148
00:11:38.740 --> 00:11:42.452
- Mmm.
- [chuckles. inhales deeply]

149
00:11:43.036 --> 00:11:45.247
What a low bar we've set these days.

150
00:11:45.330 --> 00:11:48.834
Or more precisely. they don't remember
hiring someone to kill you.

151
00:11:49.710 --> 00:11:51.170
Well. that's a loophole to close.

152
00:11:51.253 --> 00:11:53.463
Yes. I'll see to that.

153
00:11:55.299 --> 00:11:57.843
I've also edited the memories
of the medical staff.

154
00:11:57.926 --> 00:12:03.390
They'll have no recollection of having
seen either of us so compromised.

155
00:12:07.978 --> 00:12:09.813
[kisses] Enemies in my home.

156
00:12:11.690 --> 00:12:14.526
Foundation poaching the Outer Reach.

157
00:12:16.320 --> 00:12:19.156
The Empire squirms in my grasp
like an angry cat.

158
00:12:19.239 --> 00:12:24.745
which makes me all the more determined
to solidify this marriage.

159
00:12:28.207 --> 00:12:31.710
To that end. I've found someone
to engage the Foundation.

160
00:12:31.793 --> 00:12:34.505
Fifteen years' experience
in the Superluminal Armada.

161
00:12:35.088 --> 00:12:36.590
A decade in Intelligence.

162
00:12:36.673 --> 00:12:39.885
- Oh. come on!
- Honest. Incorruptible.

163
00:12:39.968 --> 00:12:41.261
Bel Riose?

164
00:12:42.262 --> 00:12:44.431
- Absolutely not.
- He's the best man for the job.

165
00:12:44.515 --> 00:12:46.850
He retreated under fire
over the Lemul Cluster.

166
00:12:46.934 --> 00:12:48.852
He executed a flanking maneuver

167
00:12:48.936 --> 00:12:50.816
and won the encounter
with minimal loss of life.

168
00:12:50.854 --> 00:12:53.440
Immaterial. He disobeyed me.

169
00:12:53.524 --> 00:12:57.152
Your efforts to extinguish the Foundation
will suffer if you indulge your ego.

170
00:12:57.236 --> 00:13:01.156
Ego? Riose thinks he can disregard
the wishes of an emperor.

171
00:13:01.240 --> 00:13:03.408
Luck happened to be on his side one time!

172
00:13:03.492 --> 00:13:07.079
And his people. extolling him
as a hero for saving their lives.

173
00:13:07.162 --> 00:13:09.581
when what he's really done
is rupture military discipline.

174
00:13:09.665 --> 00:13:12.876
How long do they think the service
will feed them and bind up their wounds

175
00:13:12.960 --> 00:13:14.962
if obeying orders becomes optional?

176
00:13:15.045 --> 00:13:19.049
It's a step into chaos.
another symptom of void-fucked entropy

177
00:13:19.132 --> 00:13:21.927
as everything goes lurching off
into disorder

178
00:13:22.010 --> 00:13:24.388
and I'm left to scrabble around
like an infant.

179
00:13:24.471 --> 00:13:27.266
looking for pieces large enough to grasp.

180
00:13:30.435 --> 00:13:32.771
From the universe to an atom...

181
00:13:34.773 --> 00:13:37.901
it all just falls apart
in your own damn hands.

182
00:13:43.407 --> 00:13:45.492
[exhales deeply]

183
00:13:49.621 --> 00:13:52.249
How long did you expect
my outburst to last?

184
00:13:52.916 --> 00:13:55.878
A minute and a quarter.
You came in well under.

185
00:13:56.962 --> 00:13:59.423
- Hmm.
- Shall I speak with Riose?

186
00:14:02.843 --> 00:14:04.344
If he refuses...

187
00:14:06.263 --> 00:14:07.264
kill him.

188
00:14:34.208 --> 00:14:37.544
- Bel Riose?
- He's the ablest general we have.

189
00:14:37.628 --> 00:14:38.921
[Dusk] Yes. and he knows it.

190
00:14:39.004 --> 00:14:41.483
And if he's out to settle scores with you.
it will get volatile.

191
00:14:41.507 --> 00:14:43.675
His fleet is extremely loyal to him.

192
00:14:43.759 --> 00:14:45.594
He has no fleet. He's a prisoner.

193
00:14:45.677 --> 00:14:48.222
Well. perhaps he should remain one.

194
00:14:48.305 --> 00:14:49.306
[fork clinks loudly]

195
00:14:50.516 --> 00:14:51.516
And please.

196
00:14:53.727 --> 00:14:54.728
Forks down.

197
00:14:54.811 --> 00:14:56.939
[forks clattering]

198
00:14:57.022 --> 00:14:58.607
As we begin again.

199
00:14:58.690 --> 00:14:59.942
[Day sighs]

200
00:15:00.025 --> 00:15:03.570
Index finger below the tines.
Arc the forearm. Arc the forearm.

201
00:15:03.654 --> 00:15:07.866
[stammers] As Prime. my brothers
would do well to follow my lead.

202
00:15:07.950 --> 00:15:11.245
Brother. your genetic match
to the Principium

203
00:15:11.328 --> 00:15:13.080
was off by three centimorgans.

204
00:15:13.163 --> 00:15:14.039
That's been corrected.

205
00:15:14.122 --> 00:15:16.750
DNA is easy. Habits are hard.

206
00:15:16.834 --> 00:15:18.752
We must present as one man.

207
00:15:18.836 --> 00:15:21.672
No matter how far you...
[stammers] ...we have drifted.

208
00:15:21.755 --> 00:15:24.091
On the subject of Riose.

209
00:15:24.174 --> 00:15:28.136
I remember learning about a similar
difficulty faced by Emperor Daluben IV.

210
00:15:28.220 --> 00:15:30.114
There was a wildly charismatic general.
and he...

211
00:15:30.138 --> 00:15:33.016
Now I have a history instructor
as well as a movement coach.

212
00:15:34.017 --> 00:15:38.730
Yet another incentive for this marriage.
We don't ever have to do this again.

213
00:15:53.579 --> 00:15:56.832
[Salvor] So. the Second Foundation.

214
00:15:56.915 --> 00:15:58.917
Why did you keep Hari from starting it?

215
00:15:59.001 --> 00:16:00.127
I don't know.

216
00:16:02.421 --> 00:16:03.964
I loved your father.

217
00:16:04.548 --> 00:16:07.885
With Raych. I finally felt whole.

218
00:16:09.094 --> 00:16:10.762
And Hari ripped that away from me.

219
00:16:11.346 --> 00:16:12.806
I knew the Plan was important.

220
00:16:12.890 --> 00:16:16.059
but in the moment.
I couldn't separate the man from the math.

221
00:16:17.311 --> 00:16:20.022
And if you had.
you could've helped Terminus?

222
00:16:20.105 --> 00:16:22.399
[sighs] It's more complicated than that.

223
00:16:22.482 --> 00:16:24.693
Hari doesn't tell you everything.
He never does.

224
00:16:24.776 --> 00:16:27.863
[Hari]
Give a girl a fish. she eats for a day.

225
00:16:30.991 --> 00:16:32.743
Teach a girl to fish...

226
00:16:33.702 --> 00:16:36.288
You've peered into
the Prime Radiant. Gaal.

227
00:16:36.371 --> 00:16:37.873
All the way to the end.

228
00:16:37.956 --> 00:16:41.126
The answers are there for you
if you care to work them out.

229
00:16:42.336 --> 00:16:47.216
We're not meant to interfere in the war
between Empire and Foundation.

230
00:16:47.299 --> 00:16:49.301
much as you might wish to.

231
00:16:49.384 --> 00:16:52.679
Well. you said the math was off course.
so let's fix it.

232
00:16:53.388 --> 00:16:54.988
I mean. they do need to win. don't they?

233
00:16:55.015 --> 00:16:59.353
We're decades from Terminus.
without a jumpship or access to a gate.

234
00:16:59.436 --> 00:17:00.604
And even if we had.

235
00:17:00.687 --> 00:17:03.649
- we wouldn't intervene directly.
- Why not?

236
00:17:03.732 --> 00:17:06.234
First Foundation needs to be
kept in the dark.

237
00:17:06.318 --> 00:17:10.196
Psychohistory predicts
the natural patterns of humanity.

238
00:17:10.781 --> 00:17:13.450
Introduce too much information
into the system.

239
00:17:13.534 --> 00:17:14.910
and you disturb it.

240
00:17:14.992 --> 00:17:17.538
which is why the system required
a counterpoint.

241
00:17:17.621 --> 00:17:18.872
A Second Foundation.

242
00:17:19.455 --> 00:17:22.084
Psychohistorians with access to the Plan.

243
00:17:22.709 --> 00:17:24.795
Knowledge of the future
applied judiciously

244
00:17:24.877 --> 00:17:28.507
and with intent to quietly adjust
the Empire's course.

245
00:17:28.590 --> 00:17:30.425
Or the First Foundation's. if needed.

246
00:17:30.509 --> 00:17:32.553
Now she gets it. Finally.

247
00:17:33.512 --> 00:17:35.347
You're talking like Terminus is the enemy.

248
00:17:35.430 --> 00:17:36.473
It isn't. Not yet.

249
00:17:36.557 --> 00:17:37.975
But power corrupts.

250
00:17:38.058 --> 00:17:41.520
And a Foundation left unchecked
becomes Empire all over again.

251
00:17:41.603 --> 00:17:44.815
They are good people.
You do not know them like I do.

252
00:17:44.898 --> 00:17:46.233
Everyone you knew there is dead.

253
00:17:47.651 --> 00:17:48.652
Nice.

254
00:17:49.236 --> 00:17:51.613
We lose. it's bad. We win. it's bad.

255
00:17:52.197 --> 00:17:54.575
I c... [scoffs] I can't accept that.

256
00:17:55.158 --> 00:17:57.318
I don't know
if the Foundation can survive this crisis.

257
00:17:57.369 --> 00:17:59.580
but I know what's ahead.

258
00:18:00.914 --> 00:18:03.208
I know what all that red
in the Radiant is.

259
00:18:03.292 --> 00:18:05.961
You felt something. Another presentiment.

260
00:18:06.837 --> 00:18:08.130
Tell me.

261
00:18:08.839 --> 00:18:10.132
Despair.

262
00:18:11.216 --> 00:18:13.135
Death. Destruction.

263
00:18:14.970 --> 00:18:16.096
I did this.

264
00:18:17.055 --> 00:18:20.017
When I climbed out of the pool
and stumbled in on you and Raych.

265
00:18:20.100 --> 00:18:21.852
I threw the equations off course.

266
00:18:24.897 --> 00:18:28.025
But maybe those same instincts
can steer them back.

267
00:18:28.734 --> 00:18:30.569
I've felt stronger since Salvor arrived.

268
00:18:30.652 --> 00:18:33.822
Maybe it's her abilities.
an amplifying effect.

269
00:18:33.906 --> 00:18:36.158
Abilities? You feel the future as well?

270
00:18:36.241 --> 00:18:37.743
Uh. not the future. The past.

271
00:18:37.826 --> 00:18:39.870
Just moments Gaal and Raych experienced.

272
00:18:40.746 --> 00:18:43.040
- Raych?
- Uh. via the seed bank.

273
00:18:43.123 --> 00:18:46.001
Um. if Salvor can access my memories.

274
00:18:46.084 --> 00:18:49.588
then maybe my premonitions
are the same thing in reverse.

275
00:18:49.671 --> 00:18:52.508
[stammers]
Memories my future self has experienced.

276
00:18:52.591 --> 00:18:56.261
Show me the turning point
where chaos seems to consume everything.

277
00:19:05.479 --> 00:19:06.605
Your turning point.

278
00:19:06.688 --> 00:19:09.274
How far into the future
would you say that is?

279
00:19:09.358 --> 00:19:11.985
Another 150 years?

280
00:19:12.069 --> 00:19:14.363
That's where you need to project
your consciousness. Gaal.

281
00:19:14.446 --> 00:19:16.156
That's where we find a new path.

282
00:19:16.240 --> 00:19:19.302
- [stammers] I should be long dead by then.
- You slept through the last century.

283
00:19:19.326 --> 00:19:21.245
Who's to say
you don't sleep through the next?

284
00:19:33.423 --> 00:19:34.633
[Day. Dawn. Dusk] Dominion.

285
00:19:39.012 --> 00:19:41.390
Lady Demerzel. will you not dine with us?

286
00:19:41.473 --> 00:19:44.476
Thank you. Your Grace.
I'm more comfortable where I stand.

287
00:19:46.854 --> 00:19:47.855
Thank you.

288
00:19:49.273 --> 00:19:52.150
I've always been fascinated
by planetesimals.

289
00:19:52.234 --> 00:19:53.902
How many in your realm are populated?

290
00:19:53.986 --> 00:19:55.904
Oh. more than a thousand
in the Cloud Dominion.

291
00:19:55.988 --> 00:19:57.155
Many with unique features.

292
00:19:57.239 --> 00:19:59.741
We'll host a visit.
and you can come ice-running with me.

293
00:19:59.825 --> 00:20:01.994
There are mountains of methane ice
to play on.

294
00:20:02.077 --> 00:20:03.412
I'd enjoy that very much.

295
00:20:04.580 --> 00:20:06.380
Will you join us for ice-running.
Brother Day?

296
00:20:06.456 --> 00:20:09.751
Steel blades on combustible ice
at high speeds?

297
00:20:09.835 --> 00:20:11.837
[Day. Dusk chuckle]

298
00:20:11.920 --> 00:20:15.716
We'll leave that to. uh.
foolish youngsters with flexible knees.

299
00:20:15.799 --> 00:20:16.799
[Sareth] Really?

300
00:20:16.842 --> 00:20:19.720
I mean. if need be.
can't you simply decant a new one of you

301
00:20:19.803 --> 00:20:20.971
and take their knees?

302
00:20:21.722 --> 00:20:22.598
Dominion.

303
00:20:22.681 --> 00:20:25.893
I'm sorry. Was that rude?
Aren't we to be family?

304
00:20:25.976 --> 00:20:28.312
Not rude at all. Curiosity is becoming.

305
00:20:28.395 --> 00:20:30.105
Well. I am fascinated.

306
00:20:30.189 --> 00:20:33.734
For example. if yesterday's
assassination attempt had succeeded.

307
00:20:34.401 --> 00:20:36.153
you'd be a new man now. wouldn't you?

308
00:20:36.236 --> 00:20:38.405
[stammers] Would we even know?
Would he know?

309
00:20:38.488 --> 00:20:39.799
How did you learn of the attempt?

310
00:20:39.823 --> 00:20:41.663
It was a only rumor
till you just confirmed it.

311
00:20:42.284 --> 00:20:44.203
There are many rumors
about Empire. you know.

312
00:20:44.286 --> 00:20:45.996
Some more frivolous than others.

313
00:20:46.079 --> 00:20:48.332
I've heard you don't lift your own forks.

314
00:20:48.957 --> 00:20:51.502
That the servants feed you
like infants. [chuckles]

315
00:20:51.585 --> 00:20:55.672
Oh. please. Astrid.
come and hoist this quail

316
00:20:55.756 --> 00:20:57.549
and shove it into my mouth.

317
00:20:57.633 --> 00:20:59.134
[Dusk. guests chuckle]

318
00:20:59.218 --> 00:21:02.554
[Sareth] Yeah. well. it must be nice
to have some surety of succession.

319
00:21:02.638 --> 00:21:05.390
If you marry me and rely on biology.
you'll lose that.

320
00:21:05.474 --> 00:21:08.143
With multiple children.
we'll have a different kind of surety.

321
00:21:08.227 --> 00:21:11.730
True. With enough children. even
a zeppelin crash needn't disrupt the line.

322
00:21:14.316 --> 00:21:15.901
We are very sorry for your losses.

323
00:21:18.862 --> 00:21:22.658
My oldest sister. the crown princess.
was trained in leadership.

324
00:21:22.741 --> 00:21:25.327
My brother was an officer
in the Royal Hussars.

325
00:21:25.410 --> 00:21:27.704
I was allowed to be a dilettante.

326
00:21:27.788 --> 00:21:31.500
Sport. art. music.

327
00:21:31.583 --> 00:21:36.421
Well. may we all be eternal students.

328
00:21:38.590 --> 00:21:41.468
Yes. it was a wonderful life
until the accident.

329
00:21:42.261 --> 00:21:46.056
Now. I am Dominion
with no education on how to rule.

330
00:21:46.139 --> 00:21:50.102
Our alliance will provide you
with all the support you could wish for.

331
00:21:51.395 --> 00:21:52.813
I see benefits to myself.

332
00:21:57.860 --> 00:21:59.403
But what of you. Brother Dawn?

333
00:22:00.988 --> 00:22:02.531
You'll lose a kingdom.

334
00:22:02.614 --> 00:22:04.116
But gain a sister.

335
00:22:04.783 --> 00:22:06.743
- Is that what I'll be?
- [chuckles]

336
00:22:08.453 --> 00:22:09.573
And won't I be accomplishing

337
00:22:09.621 --> 00:22:11.832
what yesterday's attempt sought to do
but could not?

338
00:22:11.915 --> 00:22:13.584
A baby is born.

339
00:22:13.667 --> 00:22:15.836
and all the other branches
fall off the tree.

340
00:22:15.919 --> 00:22:20.090
Assassination by procreation. [chuckles]

341
00:22:20.174 --> 00:22:23.677
Uh. we're not branches. It's all one tree.

342
00:22:23.760 --> 00:22:25.240
[Day. Dawn. Dusk] We're the same man.

343
00:22:26.722 --> 00:22:29.516
But you would never become Day.

344
00:22:29.600 --> 00:22:31.935
Your very reason for existing
would be erased.

345
00:22:32.019 --> 00:22:35.105
[chuckles] She's gonna talk
her way out of marriage.

346
00:22:35.189 --> 00:22:36.709
- [Day] Not at all.
- [Sareth chuckles]

347
00:22:37.107 --> 00:22:40.068
She's displaying a fine mind for analysis.

348
00:22:40.152 --> 00:22:41.153
May I see them. Empire?

349
00:22:42.321 --> 00:22:44.239
The branches I'll be snipping off.

350
00:22:45.240 --> 00:22:46.283
The bodies in jars.

351
00:22:51.079 --> 00:22:52.122
[chuckles]

352
00:22:53.957 --> 00:22:57.252
I will escort you
to the Principium myself.

353
00:23:00.547 --> 00:23:03.550
And please. call me "Day."

354
00:23:15.187 --> 00:23:16.980
[Rue] Dawn. Dusk.

355
00:23:32.412 --> 00:23:33.455
[Day] Cleon I.

356
00:23:33.539 --> 00:23:36.250
- Somehow. I thought he'd be lying down.
- Mmm.

357
00:23:36.333 --> 00:23:38.253
I wonder if he knew
how long he'd be on his feet.

358
00:23:38.335 --> 00:23:41.004
[chuckles] We could bring him a chair.

359
00:23:41.088 --> 00:23:43.757
I meant walking around inside you three.

360
00:23:44.883 --> 00:23:46.426
I'm not surprised he's worn out.

361
00:23:47.094 --> 00:23:48.095
[Day chuckles]

362
00:24:03.318 --> 00:24:06.029
- [Sareth] So. if you had died yesterday...
- No.

363
00:24:06.738 --> 00:24:08.824
- ...which one?
- It's this one.

364
00:24:10.909 --> 00:24:13.579
[Sareth]
"Rejoice his shame remains unknown:

365
00:24:14.246 --> 00:24:17.708
that he had almost sat a throne."

366
00:24:17.791 --> 00:24:19.126
I don't know that poem.

367
00:24:21.003 --> 00:24:22.546
It's about an uprising.

368
00:24:23.672 --> 00:24:26.300
Empire banned it decades ago.
It's a crime to quote it.

369
00:24:26.884 --> 00:24:27.884
Hmm.

370
00:24:29.428 --> 00:24:32.431
I only see Cleons.
Are the Demerzels kept separate?

371
00:24:32.514 --> 00:24:35.184
I assume
that's how she stays the same age.

372
00:24:35.267 --> 00:24:37.644
She has separate arrangements. yes.

373
00:24:38.645 --> 00:24:41.523
You can see my memories are transmitted
as I make them.

374
00:24:41.607 --> 00:24:43.650
We only edit them so he...

375
00:24:46.987 --> 00:24:49.031
so I wouldn't remember being killed.

376
00:24:49.615 --> 00:24:52.367
And he wouldn't know
he'd replaced another.

377
00:24:53.493 --> 00:24:55.370
A gift of mercy for your son.

378
00:24:55.954 --> 00:24:57.873
Or is that the wrong word?

379
00:24:57.956 --> 00:24:59.958
We call them exponents.

380
00:25:00.042 --> 00:25:04.087
It'll be easy to end them when there are
little footsteps in the palace.

381
00:25:04.755 --> 00:25:06.256
How will it be done?

382
00:25:06.340 --> 00:25:09.885
The tanks will be drained.
The decay harnessed as energy.

383
00:25:09.968 --> 00:25:11.595
Your scientists are efficient.

384
00:25:11.678 --> 00:25:13.430
Always. In fact. I have good news.

385
00:25:13.514 --> 00:25:17.267
I'm told there's little risk
of genetic disorder in our offspring.

386
00:25:17.351 --> 00:25:20.270
You tested me? [scoffs] How?

387
00:25:20.354 --> 00:25:22.314
Your drinking glass at dinner.

388
00:25:22.397 --> 00:25:25.526
I would've spat for your scientists
and eliminated a step.

389
00:25:25.609 --> 00:25:26.610
[Day] Mmm.

390
00:25:27.319 --> 00:25:28.737
So. you're expecting intercourse?

391
00:25:28.820 --> 00:25:30.656
[chuckles]

392
00:25:31.365 --> 00:25:35.494
In the pre-Cleonic age.
Empress Ravenna thought it essential.

393
00:25:36.578 --> 00:25:41.583
And I think it's a good way
to create an emotional bond.

394
00:25:44.294 --> 00:25:48.048
She also fancied a public consummation.
but that seems cruel...

395
00:25:49.299 --> 00:25:50.592
to the public.

396
00:25:53.720 --> 00:25:55.556
My sterility can be reversed.

397
00:25:55.639 --> 00:25:58.809
but I suggest that our genetic material
be combined in a lab.

398
00:25:58.892 --> 00:26:00.853
If we have a selection of viable embryos.

399
00:26:00.936 --> 00:26:04.565
we can choose one
with a superior makeup for implantation.

400
00:26:04.648 --> 00:26:07.025
Once there are children
and this room is empty.

401
00:26:07.943 --> 00:26:09.570
assassins could strike again.

402
00:26:10.070 --> 00:26:13.073
Your child would rule.
but you would be gone.

403
00:26:13.156 --> 00:26:14.616
In killing the would-be assassins.

404
00:26:14.700 --> 00:26:17.136
you've left no way to tell
if whoever sent them will send more.

405
00:26:17.160 --> 00:26:20.497
They will be deterred
by yesterday's swift justice.

406
00:26:20.581 --> 00:26:21.582
Will they?

407
00:26:22.958 --> 00:26:25.961
Dominion asks why unrest exists
and addresses causes.

408
00:26:26.044 --> 00:26:28.172
You've had a lighter hand than ours.

409
00:26:28.255 --> 00:26:30.257
A well-trimmed vessel
only needs a light hand.

410
00:26:30.340 --> 00:26:32.467
- Dominion is small.
- Empire's shrinking.

411
00:26:32.551 --> 00:26:33.844
Empire is healthy.

412
00:26:33.927 --> 00:26:35.470
Is it? [scoffs]

413
00:26:36.680 --> 00:26:38.473
'Cause there are rumors. Day.

414
00:26:38.557 --> 00:26:43.228
that the integrity of your... [scoffs]
...hermetically sealed lineage

415
00:26:43.312 --> 00:26:45.105
was corrupted some time ago.

416
00:26:45.731 --> 00:26:48.400
Which would explain. I suppose.

417
00:26:48.483 --> 00:26:54.489
your interest
in my as-yet-unexploited womb.

418
00:27:04.791 --> 00:27:07.711
[villagers clamoring in Siwennese]

419
00:27:19.014 --> 00:27:23.310
[thunder rumbling]

420
00:27:23.393 --> 00:27:25.187
Hurry up. Claric.

421
00:27:26.355 --> 00:27:27.356
[sighs]

422
00:27:33.695 --> 00:27:36.198
- [villager 1] Hey! Come back here!
- [camel bellowing]

423
00:27:54.758 --> 00:27:57.427
[grunts. yelps]

424
00:28:07.771 --> 00:28:08.856
Show tonight. [chuckles]

425
00:28:10.607 --> 00:28:11.608
Not much longer.

426
00:28:13.151 --> 00:28:15.445
Sit down if you want.
Too hot to be standing.

427
00:28:19.491 --> 00:28:20.659
Clear out!

428
00:28:20.742 --> 00:28:22.035
[children squealing]

429
00:28:23.453 --> 00:28:24.872
You gotta go. girl.

430
00:28:25.455 --> 00:28:26.999
The title is "Brother."

431
00:28:27.499 --> 00:28:30.085
Novice Claric Brother Constant
of the Foundation.

432
00:28:30.169 --> 00:28:32.379
from which all blessings are derived.

433
00:28:32.462 --> 00:28:34.798
[in Siwennese] Jori. shut her down.

434
00:28:38.927 --> 00:28:41.805
[in English]
Holo sign. Intriguing. isn't it. Jori?

435
00:28:43.056 --> 00:28:44.850
Don't you wanna see the show. Jori?

436
00:28:45.434 --> 00:28:48.187
The sign says "sunset." It's full day.

437
00:28:49.021 --> 00:28:51.398
It'll be dark soon enough.
if the Prophet wills it.

438
00:28:53.192 --> 00:28:56.153
Can I ask.
what's that you have there. sirs?

439
00:28:58.030 --> 00:28:59.907
It's called handfast.

440
00:29:00.407 --> 00:29:03.243
We use it to restrain offenders.
It's consecrated.

441
00:29:03.327 --> 00:29:05.537
A sound philosophy. restraint.

442
00:29:06.121 --> 00:29:10.751
And one the Galactic Spirit fully tends
to embrace in our celebration tonight.

443
00:29:10.834 --> 00:29:15.172
- Right. At sunset. [chuckles]
- [villagers laughing]

444
00:29:15.255 --> 00:29:16.673
[splashes]

445
00:29:16.757 --> 00:29:20.344
The Galactic Spirit in the Foundation
can help raise your crop yields.

446
00:29:20.427 --> 00:29:23.555
Keep vermin out of the harvest.
Predict weather patterns.

447
00:29:23.639 --> 00:29:25.599
All things Empire stopped doing.

448
00:29:25.682 --> 00:29:27.976
We know how to do that.

449
00:29:29.186 --> 00:29:32.439
I predict lightning.
Hits a couple tall trees every night.

450
00:29:33.232 --> 00:29:35.567
All right. You've made your speech.

451
00:29:36.443 --> 00:29:37.444
Show's over.

452
00:29:38.570 --> 00:29:40.614
[in Siwennese] Show's over!

453
00:29:40.697 --> 00:29:42.199
[powering on]

454
00:29:42.991 --> 00:29:45.577
[villagers clamoring]

455
00:29:53.794 --> 00:29:56.713
[in English] Behold the Spirit's shield.

456
00:29:56.797 --> 00:29:59.466
[in Siwennese] She's got a field
like the other blasphemer.

457
00:29:59.550 --> 00:30:01.301
[in English] Go on. Take it.

458
00:30:02.219 --> 00:30:04.304
Spirit protects anyone who believes.

459
00:30:04.388 --> 00:30:07.891
Your Spirit didn't protect
the one we strung up.

460
00:30:07.975 --> 00:30:09.935
And he was bigger than you. so...
[speaks Siwennese]

461
00:30:14.231 --> 00:30:16.191
Oh. shit. [grunts. groans]

462
00:30:17.985 --> 00:30:19.111
Claric.

463
00:30:28.412 --> 00:30:30.163
About bloody time. Claric.

464
00:30:30.247 --> 00:30:32.374
The Spirit is among us now.

465
00:30:33.834 --> 00:30:35.544
[villagers gasp]

466
00:30:36.920 --> 00:30:38.380
[Constant] Trust the Spirit.

467
00:30:46.138 --> 00:30:48.390
Greetings. people of Siwenna.

468
00:30:48.473 --> 00:30:50.726
[villagers applauding]

469
00:30:54.938 --> 00:31:00.903
The Spirit has come to free you
from fruitless labor and petty tyranny.

470
00:31:00.986 --> 00:31:03.405
Go home. heretic!

471
00:31:03.488 --> 00:31:08.285
[Jori. villagers chanting]
Go home. heretic! Go home. heretic!

472
00:31:08.368 --> 00:31:10.412
Go home. heretic!

473
00:31:10.495 --> 00:31:12.789
- Go home. heret...
- [villagers murmuring]

474
00:31:14.041 --> 00:31:15.667
[villagers gasp]

475
00:31:23.592 --> 00:31:25.219
[all laughing]

476
00:31:25.302 --> 00:31:26.929
[High Claric chuckles]

477
00:31:28.347 --> 00:31:30.807
[laughing continues]

478
00:31:30.891 --> 00:31:32.226
[camel bellows]

479
00:31:33.435 --> 00:31:34.937
He was heavier than I thought.

480
00:31:35.604 --> 00:31:39.191
I think it was these coins
he had in his pocket.

481
00:31:39.274 --> 00:31:41.985
- [villagers exclaim]
- [High Claric chuckling]

482
00:31:47.032 --> 00:31:49.034
[villagers gasp. exclaim]

483
00:31:49.117 --> 00:31:53.539
Enlightenment. citizens.
There is no end what the Spirit can do.

484
00:31:53.622 --> 00:31:54.915
Don't take it from me.

485
00:31:54.998 --> 00:31:58.877
Ask your neighbors.
seven worlds in the Outer Reach.

486
00:31:58.961 --> 00:32:02.339
once in the crushing embrace of Empire!

487
00:32:02.422 --> 00:32:05.634
And then abandoned. as you are.

488
00:32:05.717 --> 00:32:10.889
Empire cast you off.
bringing you freedom but also poverty.

489
00:32:10.973 --> 00:32:14.351
It doesn't have to be like that.
Ask Konom.

490
00:32:14.434 --> 00:32:17.813
Ask Daribow and others who are now rich.

491
00:32:17.896 --> 00:32:21.775
rich with the words of Hari Seldon.
the First Prophet.

492
00:32:21.859 --> 00:32:23.986
Remember Hari Seldon.

493
00:32:24.069 --> 00:32:26.822
That's right. Remember.

494
00:32:26.905 --> 00:32:27.906
I do.

495
00:32:27.990 --> 00:32:31.410
I saw Hari Seldon with my own eyes...

496
00:32:31.493 --> 00:32:32.703
An eyewitness.

497
00:32:32.786 --> 00:32:35.622
...138 years ago.

498
00:32:35.706 --> 00:32:39.459
And nothing since compares to that moment.

499
00:32:39.543 --> 00:32:41.128
[villagers gasp. murmuring]

500
00:32:43.797 --> 00:32:48.594
[High Claric] The Vault opened.
The Prophet emerged. He spoke.

501
00:32:48.677 --> 00:32:52.181
And those who heard his words
were forever changed.

502
00:32:52.264 --> 00:32:56.226
Gaze upon the mysteries of our faith.

503
00:32:57.019 --> 00:32:58.979
- What will they reveal?
- I want to know.

504
00:32:59.062 --> 00:33:00.981
- What was that. Brother?
- I want to know!

505
00:33:01.064 --> 00:33:02.816
She wants to know. Do you want to know?

506
00:33:02.900 --> 00:33:04.318
I wanna know!

507
00:33:04.401 --> 00:33:07.196
[villagers shouting]
I want to know! I want to know!

508
00:33:07.279 --> 00:33:12.910
Do you want to hear the good news
about the coming galactic paradise?

509
00:33:12.993 --> 00:33:14.870
- [beeping]
- [villagers] We want to hear!

510
00:33:14.953 --> 00:33:17.247
- We want to hear!
- Uh. Claric? Claric!

511
00:33:17.331 --> 00:33:18.707
[villagers] We want to hear!

512
00:33:18.790 --> 00:33:21.835
- What the damnable fuck. Brother?
- We've got to get out of here. Poly.

513
00:33:21.919 --> 00:33:23.670
[shouting. beeping continue]

514
00:33:33.639 --> 00:33:35.682
- Never heard it do that before.
- [Poly sighs]

515
00:33:35.766 --> 00:33:38.810
Must be void-damn important
not to trust sub-ether comms.

516
00:33:41.605 --> 00:33:42.856
[Poly sighs]

517
00:33:47.402 --> 00:33:49.696
What? What?

518
00:33:51.448 --> 00:33:52.491
What?

519
00:33:52.574 --> 00:33:56.036
The Vault is awake.
We've been called back to Terminus.

520
00:33:56.119 --> 00:33:57.496
Well. that's wonderful news.

521
00:33:57.579 --> 00:34:01.458
This is what you want. isn't it?
The Prophet walking amongst us again.

522
00:34:01.542 --> 00:34:04.753
One of the worst punishments
is having your wish come true.

523
00:34:05.420 --> 00:34:08.757
The second coming of Seldon
means the Second Crisis.

524
00:34:09.424 --> 00:34:11.009
[breathes shakily]

525
00:34:16.223 --> 00:34:18.183
After Seldon left the first time.

526
00:34:19.851 --> 00:34:23.522
I was sure he'd be back
once a year or a decade.

527
00:34:23.605 --> 00:34:25.315
[breathes shakily]

528
00:34:25.399 --> 00:34:31.446
But when he didn't. I thought.
"On the hundredth anniversary. surely."

529
00:34:31.530 --> 00:34:32.656
But... [sighs]

530
00:34:33.282 --> 00:34:37.119
And here we are telling people about
the Prophet who cares so much for us.

531
00:34:37.744 --> 00:34:41.665
Who lived on after death
to shepherd us through the darkness.

532
00:34:41.748 --> 00:34:43.250
Every time I preach now.

533
00:34:44.001 --> 00:34:47.838
I wonder if he's still...
is still invested in us.

534
00:34:47.920 --> 00:34:51.925
Course he is. I feel it. And you do too.

535
00:34:52.009 --> 00:34:54.386
When you tell the story
of your bearing witness to him.

536
00:34:54.469 --> 00:34:55.596
the light pours from you.

537
00:34:55.679 --> 00:34:57.054
That's flash powder. Brother.

538
00:34:57.931 --> 00:34:59.725
Flash powder and truth. Claric.

539
00:35:00.934 --> 00:35:02.644
I need a drink. [sighs]

540
00:35:02.728 --> 00:35:05.397
That's why I'm navigating. sir. [sighs]

541
00:35:05.480 --> 00:35:09.443
Already fired up neuro-drives.
Activating sleep patches.

542
00:35:10.360 --> 00:35:11.987
I'm about to engage auto-jump.

543
00:35:17.117 --> 00:35:19.870
[systems charging up]

544
00:35:27.669 --> 00:35:31.256
"Death. despair. destruction."
That's what you said.

545
00:35:31.340 --> 00:35:35.469
This certainly looks the part.
Our turning point. Go there.

546
00:35:35.552 --> 00:35:38.597
Um. I-I'm afraid if I go there.
I won't be able to find my way back.

547
00:35:38.680 --> 00:35:40.057
You need a lighthouse.

548
00:35:41.850 --> 00:35:44.102
When I'd slip into your memories.
or Raych's.

549
00:35:44.186 --> 00:35:46.480
Hugo's voice used to guide me back.

550
00:35:46.563 --> 00:35:48.106
Try listening for mine.

551
00:35:48.190 --> 00:35:51.235
- 150 years upstream?
- Why not?

552
00:35:53.111 --> 00:35:54.112
[sighs]

553
00:35:58.200 --> 00:35:59.701
[exhales deeply]

554
00:36:00.494 --> 00:36:03.747
86.988.053.

555
00:36:06.124 --> 00:36:10.003
[murmuring] 86.988.059.

556
00:36:10.087 --> 00:36:13.382
86.988.079...

557
00:36:18.720 --> 00:36:21.348
- [fist slams]
- [shouts. groans] It won't work.

558
00:36:21.431 --> 00:36:23.851
[breathing heavily]
The visions are unconscious. okay?

559
00:36:23.934 --> 00:36:26.645
I-I-I've always been asleep
or under stress. I...

560
00:36:28.272 --> 00:36:29.273
What?

561
00:36:29.356 --> 00:36:33.735
In Old Synnaxian. the word for "prophecy"
means "water takes them."

562
00:36:33.819 --> 00:36:35.445
Seers would submerge themselves.

563
00:36:35.529 --> 00:36:38.323
When they couldn't breathe.
their inner eyes opened.

564
00:36:38.407 --> 00:36:40.242
- [Salvor] Wait. Gaal!
- [breathes deeply]

565
00:36:40.325 --> 00:36:41.159
[computer] Warning.

566
00:36:41.243 --> 00:36:42.995
- Fire suppression activated.
- Wait. what?

567
00:36:43.078 --> 00:36:44.705
Venting all oxygen.

568
00:36:45.205 --> 00:36:46.248
[muttering]

569
00:36:48.458 --> 00:36:51.086
- What are you doing?
- She needs to drown. Salvor.

570
00:36:55.174 --> 00:36:56.425
[choking]

571
00:36:58.635 --> 00:37:00.596
Beggar! Emergency override.

572
00:37:00.679 --> 00:37:02.890
No! [choking] No.

573
00:37:31.251 --> 00:37:34.004
[distorted sounds of battle]

574
00:37:37.216 --> 00:37:38.258
[explosion]

575
00:37:52.814 --> 00:37:54.233
- [explosion]
- [Gaal screams]

576
00:37:54.316 --> 00:37:56.068
[grunts. whimpers]

577
00:38:01.657 --> 00:38:04.409
- [people screaming]
- [gunshots]

578
00:38:05.118 --> 00:38:06.286
[shadowy figure] Gaal!

579
00:38:10.958 --> 00:38:12.334
[weapon charging]

580
00:38:15.128 --> 00:38:16.296
[grunts]

581
00:38:18.048 --> 00:38:19.091
[screams]

582
00:38:42.614 --> 00:38:46.076
[Gaal shouts. straining]

583
00:38:51.290 --> 00:38:53.125
All alone.

584
00:38:54.793 --> 00:38:56.753
- Without your warriors.
- [whimpers]

585
00:38:57.838 --> 00:39:00.799
Where are your Mentalics. Gaal?

586
00:39:00.883 --> 00:39:03.218
Where is the Second Foundation?

587
00:39:08.557 --> 00:39:10.225
I can reach inside your mind.

588
00:39:10.893 --> 00:39:12.728
- What's that I see?
- [whimpers]

589
00:39:12.811 --> 00:39:17.524
A younger self peeking out at me.

590
00:39:17.608 --> 00:39:22.112
Are you from the Age of Empire?

591
00:39:23.155 --> 00:39:27.075
Before Hober Mallow pierced its hide.

592
00:39:27.993 --> 00:39:28.994
[Salvor] Gaal!

593
00:39:30.913 --> 00:39:32.122
Gaal?

594
00:39:33.332 --> 00:39:36.460
- [coughing. gasping]
- [Salvor] Gaal! Gaal!

595
00:39:37.836 --> 00:39:40.672
Gaal. Gaal. Gaal.

596
00:39:40.756 --> 00:39:42.883
[gasping. coughing continues]

597
00:39:42.966 --> 00:39:45.093
- Your throat.
- He was choking me.

598
00:39:45.177 --> 00:39:46.053
- [sniffles]
- Who was?

599
00:39:46.136 --> 00:39:48.138
He calls himself the Mule.

600
00:39:48.805 --> 00:39:51.099
[sighs] He's the source
of the coming darkness.

601
00:39:51.183 --> 00:39:53.185
- He's like us.
- A telepath.

602
00:39:53.268 --> 00:39:54.436
Only more powerful.

603
00:39:54.520 --> 00:39:57.981
He. uh... [swallows] He knew
I was watching him from the past from now.

604
00:39:58.065 --> 00:40:00.526
He mentioned another name. Hober Mallow.

605
00:40:00.609 --> 00:40:01.985
Hober Mallow?

606
00:40:02.069 --> 00:40:03.487
What else did you see. Gaal?

607
00:40:03.570 --> 00:40:07.032
[breathing heavily] Most of the galaxy
had already fallen at the Mule's feet.

608
00:40:07.115 --> 00:40:09.284
but he wasn't satisfied.

609
00:40:09.368 --> 00:40:12.037
- He... He wanted...
- What? He wanted what?

610
00:40:13.080 --> 00:40:14.831
...the location of the Second Foundation.

611
00:40:14.915 --> 00:40:16.500
[stammers] I knew it.

612
00:40:16.583 --> 00:40:19.044
He... He was prying it out of me.

613
00:40:20.045 --> 00:40:24.925
And when... when he looked into my mind.
I-I-I saw a glimpse inside his.

614
00:40:26.635 --> 00:40:28.136
There was so much hatred.

615
00:40:29.555 --> 00:40:31.431
Not just for me. but for everyone.

616
00:40:32.766 --> 00:40:35.853
He mentioned the word...
[stammers] ... "Mentalics." um.

617
00:40:35.936 --> 00:40:37.896
called them my... my warriors.

618
00:40:39.523 --> 00:40:41.859
He's afraid of the Second Foundation.

619
00:40:41.942 --> 00:40:44.736
Hari. he thinks they're the only thing
that can stop him.

620
00:40:45.320 --> 00:40:47.030
Then it can still exist.

621
00:40:48.240 --> 00:40:50.868
What was the location
the Mule was trying to pull out of you?

622
00:40:50.951 --> 00:40:53.620
- It's there. Go on.
- [Gaal sighs]

623
00:40:55.080 --> 00:40:58.500
Uh... [breathes shakily]

624
00:40:58.584 --> 00:41:00.794
Ig... Ig... "Ignatius"?

625
00:41:03.005 --> 00:41:05.632
No! Ignis.

626
00:41:06.216 --> 00:41:08.260
- That's a planet?
- I think so.

627
00:41:16.101 --> 00:41:18.145
[Salvor] Here it is. [sighs]

628
00:41:18.228 --> 00:41:21.648
Orbits a neutron star. It's habitable.

629
00:41:22.482 --> 00:41:25.736
And it's close.
Just under a parsec from here.

630
00:41:29.156 --> 00:41:30.949
- And I can hear...
- [indistinct whispering]

631
00:41:31.033 --> 00:41:32.910
Hear isn't quite the right word. but...

632
00:41:35.037 --> 00:41:37.664
It's almost like someone's calling to us.
Can you hear that?

633
00:41:38.582 --> 00:41:39.583
No.

634
00:41:42.711 --> 00:41:43.711
Listen.

635
00:41:46.757 --> 00:41:47.758
Maybe.

636
00:41:47.841 --> 00:41:48.842
[indistinct whispering]

637
00:41:48.926 --> 00:41:49.927
Yes.

638
00:41:50.594 --> 00:41:51.595
It feels right.

639
00:41:53.347 --> 00:41:55.599
It appears you've found us a new path.

640
00:42:17.579 --> 00:42:19.248
High Claric. welcome home.

641
00:42:19.331 --> 00:42:20.874
There's a claw in the hold.

642
00:42:20.958 --> 00:42:23.710
It's territorial.
so mind you leave her be.

643
00:42:24.670 --> 00:42:26.630
[Beki snarling]

644
00:42:34.388 --> 00:42:36.390
[in Thespin]
I'm so happy to see you. Pater.

645
00:42:36.473 --> 00:42:38.350
[Pater] You got here fast.

646
00:42:39.101 --> 00:42:41.645
They told us you were preaching
in the Red Corridor.

647
00:42:41.728 --> 00:42:43.313
[sighs. speaks Thespin]

648
00:42:43.397 --> 00:42:45.899
[in English] I like the mustache.
It looks good. [giggles]

649
00:42:46.817 --> 00:42:48.569
Everything's been crazy all day here.

650
00:42:49.111 --> 00:42:50.404
Wait till you see the Vault.

651
00:42:50.487 --> 00:42:53.282
And all of us together for it.
thank the Prophet. [chuckles]

652
00:42:53.866 --> 00:42:55.993
[in Thespin]
This portends war. doesn't it?

653
00:42:56.952 --> 00:43:00.080
[in English]
There he is. The man of the moment.

654
00:43:03.667 --> 00:43:05.961
- Shall we?
- [Constant whispers] Have faith.

655
00:43:07.004 --> 00:43:08.755
[Jaegger] Welcome back to Terminus.

656
00:43:09.298 --> 00:43:11.091
[Poly] Yeah. Good to be back.

657
00:43:11.175 --> 00:43:14.720
[Jaegger] Yeah. Nice to have you back
under such auspicious conditions.

658
00:43:20.434 --> 00:43:22.245
[Jaegger]
I convinced the Director to wait for you.

659
00:43:22.269 --> 00:43:25.397
[Poly] He would deprive himself
of my sparkling wit and company?

660
00:43:25.480 --> 00:43:27.024
He used other words.

661
00:43:28.192 --> 00:43:29.860
But you had to be a part of this.

662
00:43:31.403 --> 00:43:34.406
Poly Verisof. the Holy Witness.

663
00:43:34.489 --> 00:43:38.285
The ten-year-old half-feral child
with a front-row seat to revelation.

664
00:43:38.368 --> 00:43:41.288
I don't know about the half-feral.
but I'm honored all the same.

665
00:43:41.872 --> 00:43:43.290
Go ahead. Warden Jaegger.

666
00:43:43.373 --> 00:43:47.628
When the Prophet emerges. I'm going to ask
to speak with him privately.

667
00:43:47.711 --> 00:43:49.588
That way. we won't have any surprises.

668
00:43:49.671 --> 00:43:52.925
- Where will I be?
- With the citizens. managing the crowd.

669
00:43:53.008 --> 00:43:55.260
I'll introduce you.
You can say a homily or something.

670
00:43:55.344 --> 00:43:59.723
You want me on crowd control?

671
00:43:59.806 --> 00:44:02.226
Hari Seldon is about to walk
out of his vault

672
00:44:02.309 --> 00:44:07.314
and take note of what's been done
in his name since the last time I saw him.

673
00:44:07.397 --> 00:44:09.942
If anyone speaks alone with him.
it should be me.

674
00:44:10.025 --> 00:44:11.860
My title alone ensures it.

675
00:44:11.944 --> 00:44:14.530
High Claric didn't exist
the last time Seldon appeared.

676
00:44:14.613 --> 00:44:16.573
The Church of the Galactic Spirit
didn't exist.

677
00:44:16.657 --> 00:44:18.867
The Foundation endorses
the church's missionary work.

678
00:44:18.951 --> 00:44:21.578
but it is ultimately just recruitment.

679
00:44:21.662 --> 00:44:22.913
Just recruitment?

680
00:44:22.996 --> 00:44:24.289
And we thank you for it.

681
00:44:24.373 --> 00:44:28.085
The impending war will be funded
because you sell salvation.

682
00:44:28.168 --> 00:44:29.962
and tricks and trinkets.

683
00:44:30.045 --> 00:44:34.716
I was against that approach. by the way.
I was against calling ourselves Magicians.

684
00:44:34.800 --> 00:44:39.513
We're supposed to offer them
a rational blueprint of a new society.

685
00:44:39.596 --> 00:44:42.766
not turn them into arms depots
and military bases.

686
00:44:42.850 --> 00:44:45.394
You've always closed your eyes
to the realities of war.

687
00:44:46.436 --> 00:44:48.939
When was the last time you visited
the church here

688
00:44:49.940 --> 00:44:51.942
to see the new technologies?

689
00:44:52.025 --> 00:44:55.654
Are they deadly?
No. wait. are they expensive?

690
00:44:55.737 --> 00:45:00.158
Are we going to tax our citizens more
to pay for them?

691
00:45:00.242 --> 00:45:01.660
Are you going to get a cut?

692
00:45:02.953 --> 00:45:07.040
Look at this place.
We might as well be on Trantor.

693
00:45:07.124 --> 00:45:11.128
Seldon was a teacher. not a trader.

694
00:45:11.211 --> 00:45:17.801
His mission was to shorten humankind's
slide into barbarism and ignorance.

695
00:45:17.885 --> 00:45:20.554
- Do you still believe in that?
- I believe in the Prophet.

696
00:45:20.637 --> 00:45:22.598
Yeah? Which way are you spelling it?

697
00:45:22.681 --> 00:45:25.267
You're not speaking with him. Poly.

698
00:45:25.350 --> 00:45:27.144
Then why bother calling me home?

699
00:45:28.020 --> 00:45:29.438
You're popular with the masses.

700
00:45:29.521 --> 00:45:31.857
I'm not some damn painting of a saint.

701
00:45:32.691 --> 00:45:35.611
I'm the last one alive
who saw him in person.

702
00:45:36.195 --> 00:45:39.198
And when he looks at
what's been done in his name.

703
00:45:39.281 --> 00:45:41.575
I'm the only one
who can explain it to him.

704
00:45:42.242 --> 00:45:43.744
You see it. Warden Jaegger?

705
00:45:43.827 --> 00:45:45.162
You want the truth?

706
00:45:46.371 --> 00:45:48.123
I can smell liquor on you.

707
00:45:48.832 --> 00:45:51.919
And your pupils. Vordaline dust maybe?

708
00:45:52.002 --> 00:45:53.420
Do I seem drunk?

709
00:45:54.046 --> 00:45:56.423
I want people next to me
with steady hands.

710
00:45:56.507 --> 00:45:58.693
[director] I'd retire you
if I thought she'd stand for it.

711
00:45:58.717 --> 00:46:00.844
I shudder to think of her safety.

712
00:46:00.928 --> 00:46:02.304
You go too far. Sermak.

713
00:46:02.971 --> 00:46:05.349
Look. you guys have it out another time.

714
00:46:05.432 --> 00:46:06.934
The Vault's as ripe as a melon.

715
00:46:07.017 --> 00:46:09.811
and we can't risk another minute
for it to burst open without us.

716
00:46:11.146 --> 00:46:14.358
"You can say a homily." Fuck.

717
00:46:18.278 --> 00:46:21.031
[Sermak]
My girl. [sighs] I'm so glad you're back.

718
00:46:21.114 --> 00:46:23.575
[chuckles] Dad. Me too.

719
00:46:24.493 --> 00:46:26.995
I'm just so glad
I get to be with my whole family

720
00:46:27.079 --> 00:46:28.330
when we witness the Prophet.

721
00:46:29.706 --> 00:46:32.584
I have to oversee the final preparations.
I'll see you at the Vault.

722
00:46:39.174 --> 00:46:42.886
[Poly] This is a mistake.
I can feel it in my bones.

723
00:47:16.378 --> 00:47:19.256
I never got to plant my flag here
when I was a boy.

724
00:47:44.072 --> 00:47:48.076
Hari Seldon.
if it please you to show yourself...

725
00:47:53.207 --> 00:47:57.169
Dr. Seldon. I walk behind you.

726
00:47:57.252 --> 00:48:01.715
To walk beside you for one step
would fulfill every dream.

727
00:48:05.093 --> 00:48:07.179
More than one step would be good too.

728
00:48:12.142 --> 00:48:13.560
[citizens gasping]

729
00:48:29.284 --> 00:48:30.994
[citizens murmuring]

730
00:48:39.336 --> 00:48:41.797
Dr. Seldon. Hari Seldon!

731
00:48:43.507 --> 00:48:45.008
Maybe he wants us to enter.

732
00:48:46.969 --> 00:48:48.303
Shall I join you. sir?

733
00:48:52.683 --> 00:48:56.979
People of Terminus.
I am beyond proud today

734
00:48:57.062 --> 00:49:00.148
to bear the title "Warden of Terminus."

735
00:49:00.232 --> 00:49:04.278
The same title borne
by the great Salvor Hardin

736
00:49:04.361 --> 00:49:06.530
the last time this vault opened!

737
00:49:08.824 --> 00:49:14.830
There have been days
when the burden of the job. of her legacy.

738
00:49:15.831 --> 00:49:17.499
weighed heavy on me.

739
00:49:17.583 --> 00:49:20.419
but today makes it all worth it!

740
00:49:20.502 --> 00:49:25.591
Today. I will speak to the Prophet!
I will bring back his word!

741
00:49:25.674 --> 00:49:29.636
And then I will lead you all
whither he sends us!

742
00:49:29.720 --> 00:49:31.805
"Whither"? Jackass.

743
00:49:31.889 --> 00:49:34.057
He didn't even introduce me.

744
00:49:34.141 --> 00:49:38.854
Let me hear you
as I step boldly into the future!

745
00:49:38.937 --> 00:49:40.647
[cheering]

746
00:49:54.494 --> 00:49:55.495
[gasps]

747
00:49:58.957 --> 00:50:00.751
[grunts] Hober Mallow.

748
00:50:02.836 --> 00:50:04.004
Hober Mallow.

749
00:50:05.255 --> 00:50:10.093
Hober Mallow! Hober Mallow! Hober Mallow!

750
00:50:10.719 --> 00:50:13.430
Get Hober Mallow!

751
00:50:15.140 --> 00:50:16.934
[citizens screaming]

752
00:50:28.987 --> 00:50:31.031
Who the heck is Hober Mallow?

753
00:50:31.990 --> 00:50:33.033
Shit.

754
00:50:41.959 --> 00:50:42.959
[inhales sharply]

755
00:50:43.669 --> 00:50:45.170
[breathes shakily]

756
00:51:01.061 --> 00:51:02.062
Gaal?

757
00:51:04.439 --> 00:51:05.440
Gaal?

758
00:51:24.501 --> 00:51:26.753
- Gaal?
- Maybe this is a mistake.

759
00:51:26.837 --> 00:51:29.047
Maybe we're playing
right into the Mule's hands.

760
00:51:30.966 --> 00:51:31.967
Why do you say that?

761
00:51:32.843 --> 00:51:34.386
I need to tell you something.

762
00:51:36.513 --> 00:51:38.098
You saw something else. didn't you?

763
00:51:38.182 --> 00:51:41.852
[breathing shakily] My vision of the Mule.
I. um... I hid something.

764
00:51:43.312 --> 00:51:45.022
From you and... and Hari.

765
00:51:45.105 --> 00:51:46.773
[grunting]

766
00:51:46.857 --> 00:51:48.692
I was trying to escape him.

767
00:51:51.486 --> 00:51:56.992
There was ash everywhere.
The smell of human flesh burning.

768
00:52:04.791 --> 00:52:05.792
[screams]

769
00:52:06.335 --> 00:52:08.879
[coughs. groans]

770
00:52:08.962 --> 00:52:11.840
He knocked me down. and I was stunned. I...

771
00:52:13.300 --> 00:52:14.468
I turned...

772
00:52:14.551 --> 00:52:16.094
[grunting]

773
00:52:20.641 --> 00:52:22.392
I saw you lying next to me.

774
00:52:35.155 --> 00:52:36.615
[breathes shakily]

775
00:52:36.698 --> 00:52:38.075
You were dead.

776
00:52:39.117 --> 00:52:42.955
Salvor... [sobs] ...you were dead.

776
00:52:43.305 --> 00:53:43.201
